Package: chumby-player
Version: @VERSION@
Architecture: arm64
Maintainer: Jan <jan@simula.no>
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Depends: cage, mpv, pipewire-alsa, python3, 7zip | p7zip-full, libc6, libgcc-s1, libfontconfig1, libssl3t64, libasound2t64, libudev1
Description: Chumby control panel player (chumby-fork Ruffle kiosk)
 Runs the original Chumby Classic control panel under a patched Ruffle
 inside a cage Wayland kiosk on tty1. Installing this package and
 enabling chumby-player.service turns the Pi into "player mode"; SSH
 stays available, and "systemctl disable --now chumby-player" is the
 escape hatch.
 .
 Ships everything except the copyrighted chumby firmware files:
 chumby-download-firmware fetches them from Chumby's servers, or copy
 them from your chumby or its backup into /var/lib/chumby — the
 launcher prints the exact paths when something is missing.
 .
 Library dependencies match the NEEDED entries of the shipped binary
 on Debian trixie (Raspberry Pi OS base); the package is still built
 with plain dpkg-deb, not as a policy-compliant Debian source package.
